Rating: 4
Delicious dish, though I admit I made quite a few modifications... I had a green bell pepper I needed to use so I sliced it, along with a yellow onion, and cooked them along with the tomatillos and garlic in the broth. I substituted a poblano pepper and a fresh jalapeno for the serrano chile as that was what I had on hand. Next time I'll add another jalapeno as it wasn't spicy enough for my taste. I blistered the tortillas over an open flame on the stove before layering and, as suggested by other reviewers, used Queso Fresco in place of the mozzarella. I liked the flavor of the cheese but it didn't get melty as mozzarella would have. I may try a combination of both next time. I layered as directed in the recipe but then added a final, extra layer of tortilla, mozzarella and sauce. In place of the whipping cream I loosened some sour cream with a bit of milk. I served it with some of the loosened sour cream drizzled over the top and a garnish of extra cilantro and green onion. It came out a tiny bit dry so next time I may cover with foil and then just brown the top under the broiler.

