I live in San Diego with great mexican food, and the idea of Mozarella cheese in an enchilada dish seemed strange. So I used queso fresco as someone else suggested. The taste was good but is was not the right kind of cheese for this dish-- it is a type of farmers cheese and didn't melt into the dish. Next time I will try either the mozzarella or a mix of jack and cheddar (or I will ask at the taco shops what kind of cheese they use for their enchiladas!) Initially the tomatillo sauce was a little bland. I added some lemon juice, red wine vinegar, and sugar (along with salt) to give it a little tanginess. The heat from one large serrano chile w/seeds was fine for average taste buds. I forget the cream altogether and the dish was still very good. It is great make ahead dish. I added guacamole and chips, mexican rice and Caesar salad and had an easy make ahead meal for company.

