This recipe is outstanding! It is easy, delicious pure 'comfort food.' I followed the advice of others on here and used the real Mexican cheese, 'Queso Fresca,' from Oaxaca.. if you can find it. Makes all the difference in the world. I also added about a tablespoon of finely diced Jalapeno pepper (without the seeds or ribs) to the sauce. I did NOT use the whipping cream! (Too much fat and not necessary.) I substituted 1/4 cup of whole milk, which I had on hand, and drizzled it over the top. Lastly, I poured ALL the remaining tomatillo sauce over the top of the dish, rather than keeping any to serve later. I think it added to the moistness of the casserole.

