This was a huge hit. I used skinless chicken breasts that I grilled on the George Forman. I also used cojita cheese as suggested by others...so I used 1/2 mozz. cheese and 1/2 cojita. Added extra serrano for some more kick. It was awesome...everyone ate it up!!

Rating: 3
Amazingly easy! I did make a few modifications: I doubled the required cilantro, added a touch more broth as a result, used both mozzarella cut into strips and thinly sliced, along with some grated Manchego, and finally, used two serrano chiles...we like things spicy, and served it with a wonderful dry Cava and Tempranillo...perfect dinner party.

Rating: 3
This was very good and pretty easy. If you're a stickler for following the recipe, read no further. I used canned tomatillos (it's essentially a casserole, c'mon, be lazy!), 2 jalapenos, and substituted Pepper Jack for the mozzarella. I also sprinkled crumbled cotija cheese and chili powder on the top. I don't think that it would have been as flavorful without the substitutions.....

