Rating: 4
I made this really simple by mixing about 1/2 to 3/4 cup of chicken broth with a large jar of Trader Joe's tomatillo salsa, then reduced it for about 20 minutes. I also used half pepper jack cheese. It was fantastic! The color of the salsa changed, but it wasn't horrifying.

Rating: 2
I made this last night for the in-laws. We were excited because the sauce looked gorgeous and smelled delicious when making it. We were all disappointed by the look of the dish after cooking. I expected the color of the green to change with the heat, but it was really unappealing to the eye without anything else going on. Perhaps I will try to add some tomatoes or something. Even regular salsa on the side didn't keep everyone from talking about the nasty color. My oldest said it looked like he was eating boogers. Goes to show how important appearance is to a dish. We did really enjoy the flavor, I may keep playing with it.

Rating: 4
This is one of my new favorites. My boyfriend and I made this together while sipping margaritas and had a fun fiesta night. We noted that next time, we'll add another chile for more heat and we'll make 1/2 MORE sauce to use for leftovers. Our variations included some cheddar cheese for color and we served it with a dollop of sour cream. Perfect for parties!

